40|$|Horiko, {{literary}} meaning digging person, {{was used}} for artisans between the 19 th {{and the beginning of}} the 20 th century in a limited area in Tokamachi city and <b>Oziya</b> in Niigata. Horiko artisans built streets and dug tunnels according to a record from the mid- 19 th century. Horiko artisans were also known for their involvement in constructing houses and warehouses. An old document regarding construction work shows that a Horiko artisan family later worked as a stone mason. This example indicates that Horiko artisans were engaged in fundamental parts of construction related to digging land and dealing with stones. However, it has not yet completely revealed what construction work Horiko artisans were involved in...|$|E

